- white-labeling
- selling modified builds
- bundling FST into a paid software product
- bundling FST into a paid production workflow/toolkit as a paid feature
- offering FST or a modified version as the primary or material value of a paid product or service
- using FST branding, logo, or icon commercially
- using FST internally as a material part of a paid client service where the software contributes meaningful commercial value, unless written permission is granted

